==English==
===Noun===
'''bowl''' ([[bowls]])

# A concave container used to hold or mix food, or present food -- such as salad or fruit -- on a table.
# The ball rolled by players in the game of [[lawn bowls]].
# A round hair cut (also known as pudding bowl or bowl cut).
# A round crater (or similar) in the ground.
# The action of bowling a ball.

====Derived terms====
*[[bowl cut]]<!-- a hairstyle, maybe hyphenated -->

